author: Jun Hao Chuang (Benchuang)
text: I joined as first-timer and was fortunate to be coached by Frederick. He guided me patiently on how to use the machines correctly and helped adjust my posture to get the most out of every workout. He also provided me with a practical diet plan, and within a week of consistent training and following the plan, I managed to lose about 3kg. I really appreciate his guidance and the supportive environment here, it‚Äôs been a great start to my fitness journey.

author: Dev Subramaniam
text: Have been to this gym for more than 5 years. I met frederick (male PT) only relatively recently at the gym, when he approached me of his own accord after overhearing a conversation I had with a fellow gym-goer about my upcoming men's physique show. Ever since, he has been extremely forthcoming and helpful, taking the time to teach me how to pose, knowing that I had been preparing myself up to this point. He has demonstrated tremendous expertise in all matters bodybuilding related, and it comes as no surprise considering his long list of achievements as both a competitor and coach. I am truly grateful to him for his generosity and kindness - if he has helped me so much thus far as a friend with no expectations of receiving an engagement, just imagine how much he can help you as your personal trainer. I highly recommend him to all fitness enthusiasts regardless of experience or background.

author: Bryan Du

Other than that, recommend all to try this gym out, its awesome.

author: Shi Yun Lim
text:
As a member, I had a positive experience with excellent service and fast response times. However, when I wanted to cancel my subscription, it was disappointing that my emails and text messages went unanswered despite multiple follow-ups.

I was happy to support their business, but their management of the cancellation of subscription has made me think otherwise. We need a one month lead time to cancel the subscription, which I followed, but due to the lack of reply on their end, it would be unlikely that I can get it cancelled timely. It is disappointing that the good service is conditional.

Does require a lot of housekeeping. The functional area needs to be neatened up and the floor mats might need to be replaced, and the benches need to be changed too.

It would be good to enforce better rules (BIG SIGNS) so members know how one should place the weights back after using them. It is more of a member problem, but it might help if members often see staff on the floor doing their duty to tidy up. Seeing a messy unkept gym is a turnoff and it spoils the mood for workout.

He is able to pinpoint the mistakes in my technique with expert precision just from knowing where the strains and soreness are on my body. On top of that, he gives great analogies that would significantly improve your technique. It is worth your while to be guided by JK on your fitness journey.

author: ZJ (Zozo)
text:
Nice spacious, clean and well equipped gym. Shower rooms are quite basic.

Staff are friendly and efficient in responding to quires and understanding when you are recovering from Covid (partial month membership fee waived!). Felt cared for and a peace of mind.

Personal Trainer JK was knowledgeable, very patient, encouraging, friendly and professional; sharing all aspects of fitness and health knowledge (muscular system, posture, nutrition, sleeps, etc). Having trained with him close to a year now, I feel stronger, fitter, healthier and stamina have improved a lot. Very happy and appreciate his help towards my fitness goals and learned a lot from him. Now knows how to use the machines and workout properly with the right posture. Grateful to have him as my PT for the first time.

Overall experience of the gym: My first gym experience that is not intimidating.

Thank you AF Woods Square Team.

author: Val Lim
text:
Bad experience with their staff. Their cancellation policies before meeting the 18 month minimum commitment period does not make any sense.

I have to pay one month gym membership fee in full on top of a $100 cancellation fee even though I was asked to stop strenuous exercise with immediate effect (with doctor memo).
I wrote in to appeal to waive off the one month membership because I can‚Äôt use the facilities at all with immediate effect as advised by my doctor.

I wonder how am I supposed to predict that I will be unwell and email AF 1 month in advance to avoid paying 1 month of gym membership for nothing?

If i were to use the gym for a month while claiming that I am unfit, then what purpose will the doctor memo serve? Wouldn‚Äôt the memo be a scam?

Hence, their cancellation rules are really rigid, contradicting and unreasonable.
Do read carefully and consider all aspects before signing up unless you are willing to pay while not using the facilities at all.

There are many other gyms w more flexible rules.

text:

I was also training with JK. He's helped me greatly with my fitness journey by teaching me the basics and more. I suffer from various health issues that make it difficult for me to become fit safely. Despite that, JK was very patient and managed to tailor a perfect plan for me according to my health. His willingness to help me really motivated me. I'd highly recommend this gym if you're looking to get a personal trainer, as JK will probably be one of the most insightful, kind, and helpful trainer you'll find!

JK has been very patient and very encouraging, always pushing me to my limits. I have benefitted a lot from his sessions. The knowledge acquired from him has also enabled me to use the various equipment with confidence, and not just hover around the same machines all the time.

text:
When my personal trainer JK moved to this branch of anytime fitness I moved to this branch as well to continue my sessions. Despite having the option to go to any of the numerous branches anytime fitness has all over Singapore, I travel from the east twice a week for my sessions. Never having had a personal trainer before, it was extremely nerve wrecking when I made the decision to engage a personal trainer. I could not have gotten a better PT.

Not only is he very knowledgeable and encouraging he is also extremely patient. While he will push you to your limit, he is very mindful to ensure that injuries are prevented. Above all else he is very empathetic and ensures that both your physical and mental health are taken care of.

author: Nor Syahid
text:
Pros:
- Quite spacious
- A variety of equipments including 3 power racks.

Cons:
- Always crowded
- Barbells/Dumbells/Plates are too rusty
- Free weights area too cramped
- A number of the users lack gym etiquette. "Chopeing" machines. Do not rerack after using weights.
- Too many "social media influencers" with tripods around taking up space. So you'll have watch where you walk so as not to "interfere" or be in their workout videos.
- At a particular timing, there'll be groups of kids/guys working out in a group whilst clowning around and hogging up equipments.

Conclusion:
Not a great gym if you're serious about working out.
Not a great crowd and their choice of music is not the kind that you'll be hyped about.
There are better gyms out there.

He is so good that I am willing to travel from west to north for my training!

I have been with JK for about 2 years now and I can see major improvements and see myself becoming healthier.

He is very knowledgeable and ensure that my past injuries are not aggravated and to ensure I do not sustain any new injuries. He is very patient yet firm and ensures that all my training needs are met. Thank you JK for helping me for the past 2 years and looking forward to continuing working with you.
